custom.caption: A lot of the Oregon Coast is made of these sandstone cliffs which are unsurprisingly not very robust. Pipes like this one, slowly decaying onto the beach, are pretty common. A few decades ago, you'd also see a lot of houses looking like they were one or two big storms away from dropping into the ocean.
